body:
this continues  #50479. as said [here](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/50479#issuecomment-393512359) there still a few cases missing, esp. 2 looks weird. It seems like the message is interpreted as some kind of default increment, I'd expect an infinite progress in the absence of discrete increments.

![jun-01-2018 11-17-25](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1794099/40833213-88038292-658d-11e8-930a-96ce7b59b0d5.gif)

```ts
        await vscode.window.withProgress(
            {
                location: vscode.ProgressLocation.Notification,
                title: "Test 2: report only message"
            },
            async (progress) => {
                await wait1();
                for (let i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
                    progress.report({ message: `message ${i}` });
                    await wait2();
                }
            });
```
